<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[146,770,1600,1766]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[146,244,1629,1648]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Discussion</emphasis>
. This species has a very limited distribution on 
<collectingRegion box="[690,769,1629,1648]" country="Indonesia" name="Sulawesi Utara" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Sulawesi</collectingRegion>
and nearby islands in 
<collectingCountry box="[352,443,1658,1677]" name="Indonesia" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
. They build nests in forested areas, and around human habitations, nests have been found under leaves and on fences. It is a small-bodied, dark-colored 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[601,655,1718,1736]" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Vespa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[601,655,1718,1736]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Vespa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Overall, its biology is poorly known (Matsuura and Yamane 1984, 
<bibRefCitation author="Archer" box="[648,762,1746,1765]" firstAuthor="Archer" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="43 - 50" refId="ref11948" refString="Archer, M. E. 1999. Taxonomy, distribution and nesting biology of Vespa binghami, V. basalis, V. variabilis, V. fervida, V. luctuosa, V. multimaculata and V. bellicosa. Entomol. Monthly Mag. 135: 43 - 50." type="journal article" year="1999">Archer 1999</bibRefCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
